Speech therapy as an applying science: subject, object, methods. Principles of speech therapy. Identification of speech and language disorders. Principles of assessment in speech therapy. The role of speech therapist in helping children with SEN. An overview of speech disorders.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give basic understanding of speech therapy as science, work of a speech therapist and introduce widespread speech and language disorders of children and adult.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student knows principles of speech therapy. The student understands the role of speech therapist in helping people with special needs. The student is able to identify children and adults with speech and language disorder. The student knows the principles of supporting communication.
